 with the NASA's Neutron star Interior Composition Explorer\n(NICER) X-ray telescope. A comparison of the theoretical results with\nobservational data does not exclude the possibility of quark deconfinement in\nthe interiors of compact stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 31 Jul 2022 16:32:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-09"}
